727481f-a.text:
102-53 Nicholls Avenue, adjoining the N. W. corner of 104th Street. This old house appears on an 1891 atlas of Corona. The property was owned by H. E. Sanford in 1873. The avenue was then named Vine Street.
P. L Sperr  October 2, 1935
